This repository contains my learning notes, examples, and exercises on Golang fundamentals. It covers essential Go concepts, from setting up the environment to writing test cases.

Topics Covered:
✅ Introduction to Golang: Basics, syntax, and Go toolchain
✅ Setting up Golang environment (Go installation, GOPATH, modules)
✅ Version control with Git and GitHub/GitLab
✅ Writing first Go program (Hello World, functions, loops, conditionals)
✅ Understanding Go data types, structs, maps, and interfaces
✅ Error handling and logging in Go
✅ Unit testing in Go using the testing package
